{
  "slug": "logs-are-a-user-interface",
  "title": "Logs are a user interface",
  "category": "coding",
  "kicker": "Debuggability",
  "hook": "Someone will read your logs at 2 a.m. Design for that person.",
  "readMinutes": 5,
  "date": "2026-06-20",
  "tags": [
    "logging",
    "observability"
  ],
  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Logs without context are confetti",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">A line that says \"failed\" is technically a log and practically useless. The future reader needs who, what, where, why now, and which request ties it together.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "logs · before and after",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "ERROR failed",
              "c": "err"
            },
            {
              "t": "ERROR payment_retry_failed user=42 invoice=in_9 retry=3 request=req_abc",
              "c": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "change",
          "nodes": [
            "tests",
            "API",
            "data",
            "logs",
            "review",
            "deploy"
          ],
          "caption": "A tiny patch rarely touches only one thing. Push it and watch the review surface appear.",
          "action": "ship the diff",
          "idle": "change looks calm",
          "running": "checking blast radius...",
          "done": "6 engineering checks touched"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Log facts, not panic",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Use structured fields for ids, state, attempt counts, durations, and decision points. Avoid logging secrets, blobs, or poetic stack traces with no handle.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "logger.info.js",
          "code": "logger.warn(\"payment_retry_failed\", {\n  userId, invoiceId, attempt, requestId,\n  reason: error.code\n});",
          "caption": "Structured logs are easier to search, alert, and join."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Sample the noisy path",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Logs should explain rare failures without drowning normal traffic. Put more context near state transitions and fewer words in hot loops.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "change confidence lab",
